</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>At 1x you can insure 5% of the amount, then 10%, and so on up to 100%. After each use of this feature, the percentage increases. Another interesting feature is selling bets. It allows you to get the winnings before the deal is settled. Of course, the profit will be less, but on the other hand, if you wait until the end of the match, the bet may even lose. At other operators, this function is sometimes called early redemption.
    </p>

</div>

<div class="heads brown">
    <h3>What does "insure betting" mean?</h3>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>In practice, it means that if the bet loses you will get back a part of the whole amount.</p>

</div>



<div class="heads green">
    <h2>Possible strategies</h2>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>In this organization, you can freely use any strategies except forks. Here are some of the more popular ones:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>fixed percentage</b> - the same proportion of the betting amount for all bets;</li>
        <li><b>Catch-up</b> - the amount of each bet is calculated to cover the previous failures and to obtain the desired profit (the player regulates it himself);
        </li>
        <li><b>Martingale system</b> - the sum is each time increased by 2 times in case of losing, that allows covering all failures with one winning;
        </li>
        <li><b>Kelly criterion</b> - the amount is calculated according to the formula: (bookmaker's odds probability according to player's opinion/100 - 1) / (bookmaker's odds - 1);
        </li>
        <li><b>Flat</b> - fixed amount per event;
        </li>
        <li><b>Ladder</b> - we use events with the minimum risk (with odds up to 1.3), we put the sum won at the previous step on the next event until we reach a certain sum.
        </li>
    </ul>

